'He's
a memorable character, a dangerous person in any setting,' Jason 
January, the former Dallas County district attorney who in 1999 
prosecuted Feldman for capital murder, said earlier this week. 'He threatened to kill me 
personally.'

The dead man's two truck 
driver victims were killed about 45 minutes apart on August 24, 1998. 
Prosecutors said Feldman became enraged after Everett cut him off, so he
shot him and then later, simply because he was still angry, shot 
Velasquez.

Feldman was the 503rd inmate to be put to death in Texas since reinstatement.

